text=:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a:Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a:Title: Accent discrimination in higher education%0a:Author: ruiranx%0a:Section: F%0a:Completed: 01.05.2021 - 20:56%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210512-122736-676080#%0a* [-12.05.2021 - 05:27-] || TA_mason marked as complete%0a#foxend 210512-122736-676080#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0aSummary: \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aProfessors with Asian and Korean surnames were given worse ratings on clarity of teaching%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aThis article from 2015 [1] describes a study of professor ratings on Rate My Professors (RMP). The study showed that collegiate instructors with Chinese and Korean surnames generally received lower "clarity" and "helpfulness" ratings than those with more prevalent surnames in the United States. The paper itself [2] dives deeper into corpus analysis of data from RMP, noting in particular that Asian professors' accents are frequently mentioned in feedback, and this extra consideration given to accent results in extreme positive instructors evaluations being far less frequent for Asian professors.%0a%0aThis study explores accent bias in higher education, which is an example of linguistic discrimination. The themes of nativeness evoked in these comments are in fact concerning; any professors teaching in university are more than qualified to do so, and whether their manner of teaching is marked by an accent should not have to be a significant factor. %0a%0a[1] https://www.npr.org/sections/codeswitch/2015/03/05/390686619/study-at-rate-my-professor-a-foreign-accent-can-hurt-a-teachers-score%0a[2] https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/language-in-society/article/she-does-have-an-accent-but-race-and-language-ideology-in-students-evaluations-of-mathematics-instructors-on-ratemyprofessorscom/1D4C9E099B351BADE27C9211526C4E01%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_mason:)
